tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows an elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control and possible diabetes or prediabetes, despite a normal fasting glucose. Renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are within normal limits. Mildly decreased total CO₂ may suggest a tendency toward mild metabolic acidosis. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of diabetes management and further evaluation of acid-base status if clinically indicated.
